main event: A civilian reported seeing a white, disc-shaped object over Silver Springs, Maryland on April 16, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed for a total duration of 10 minutes and 30 seconds.
The object appeared to be solid and sharply outlined.
The object moved north, then made a right-angle turn and departed.
The witness reported the object was brighter than the brightest stars.
The witness estimated the angular size of the object to be 13.5 degrees.
photographs: no, the report indicates there were no photographs
